  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "To determine if someone has read your direct message on Instagram, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Check for Read Receipts**:\n   - If the recipient has read receipts enabled, you will see \"Seen\" or their profile picture next to the message indicating that they have read it.\n\n2. **Check Message Status**:\n   - Open the conversation with the person you sent the message to.\n   - Look under the message you sent. If it says \"Seen\" or shows the recipient's profile picture, it means they have seen the message.\n\n3. **Observe Activity**:\n   - If the recipient starts typing or replies, it\u2019s a clear indication they have read your message.\n   - If they liked your message or responded with an emoji, it also indicates they have seen it.\n\nRemember, these indicators only work if the recipient has read receipts enabled. If read receipts are disabled, you may not be able to know definitively whether the message was read or not.",
